full_title: BACK TO ME by ¥$, Kanye West & Ty Dolla $ign (Ft. Freddie Gibbs)
title: BACK TO ME

description.plain:
“BACK TO ME” sees Ye and Ty Dolla $ign expand upon sexual subject material supported by Freddie Gibbs. Both Ye and Gibbs express their sexual interests while Ty Dolla $ign captures a lingering confidence, assuring his sexual partner she’ll return to him the next day.

The track originated as a dance song but evolved into a drum-ridden melody during VULTURES sessions in Japan. On October 2, 2023, then at Italy, a video clip of Ye and Ty Dolla $ign listening to “BACK TO ME” surfaced; accompanied by an unheard piano. An extended snippet surfaced two weeks later, containing a Quavo verse. However, when it debuted entirely on December 12, 2023 at the Miami VULTURES Rave, Quavo’s verse was removed in favor of Freddie Gibbs.
